item.title: Need server help.....dont read if your just going to ignore it
item.dc:creator: @xXSh0ckXx xXSh0ckXx
item.description:
@xXSh0ckXx wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:6, topic:537188”][quote author=xXSh0ckXx link=topic=656002.msg4390677#msg4390677 date=1387393048]

In your command class, add something like this.

if(command.equalsIgnoreCase("king")) { teleportX = x; // put whatever x coordinate here teleportY = y; // put whatever y coordinate here }

Pi Newfag.

@ if(playerCommand.startsWith("King")) { c.getPA().startTeleport(X, Y, 0, "modern"); //change "modern" to "ancients" if you like to, but it depends which name the Teleport handler uses c.sendMessage("Message here"); }

Make sure you also have this command:

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("mypos")) { c.sendMessage("X: "+c.absX+" Y: "+c.absY+" H: "+c.heightLevel); }
[/quote]
Why don’t you use the ternaries (or an if-else statement) so the teleport anim/gfx is based off of what book the player is on?

c.getPA().startTeleport(0, 0, 0, c.playerMagicBook == 0 ? "modern" : "ancient");[/quote] Well, this is another way, but in this case i’d set only one style of teleporting, which i think isn’t so bad. & Nice idea.
